          <td width="30">&nbsp;</td>
          <td width="405" class="texte">
FULL TIME POSITION Bordeaux, France<BR><BR>As part of the project to develop the latest version of our technology, ExEn (an embedded Java engine which permits the download of games onto mobile phones), you will be responsible for the creation, development and optimisation of our technology in an embedded environment. <BR><BR><BR>PRINCIPLE DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES<BR><BR> You will define and develop (in Java) the next version of the ExEn technology<BR> You will ensure that all these software developments are compatible with a Java Virtual Machine<BR> You will keep up to date on all technological evolutions and propose improvements to the tools and methods used by the development team<BR><BR><BR>EDUCATION, EXPERIENCE AND SKILLS REQUIRED<BR><BR> You have a degree (Bachelors or Masters equivalent) in Computer Science<BR> You are very experienced in Java programming and are familiar with Java platforms such as J2ME, J2SE, J2EE<BR> You have at least 5 years experience in software development for industrial projects <BR> Ideally, you have some experience in the mobile phone industry or in a similarly relevant domain (Pocket PC, games development).  Some knowledge of MIDP is preferable<BR> Knowledge of object-oriented software design and analysis methods would be a definite advantage<BR> A good level French and some English are necessary for this position <BR><BR>If you are a flexible, proactive individual and you are eager to participate in the growth of a highly international company, then please send us your CV.<BR><BR>We feel it is very important to help develop the skills of all our employees.  Thus, in order to help you along your career path, we do our best to maximize the possibility of internal promotion.<BR><BR>Do not forget to mention the reference RD0503Ex/IF<BR><BR><BR>
